Package fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.heaps

Class HashQueue<E>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.heaps.HashQueue<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of the elements in the hash queue.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Queue<E>
public final class HashQueue<E> extends AbstractCollection<E> implements Queue<E>
The HashQueue defines a queue with constant-time access to any of its elements. Note that an element can appear at most once in the queue. The queue also allows to access to its internal representation (which is linked-list based) so that any low-level operation can be performed efficiently from outside when needed.
